The paper focuses on the validation of machine learning-based systems, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The use of entropy-based test generation and data quality assessment is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also discusses the detection of mislabeled data, which is a security and privacy (cs.CR) concern. Finally, the user study conducted to validate the results falls under the social and information sciences (cs.SI) category.
